messages.text: The plane engine just caught fire!
I saw it burst into flames!!
Omg Rob … You’re freaking me out
I’m sitting right behind the wing, at the window
It lit up for a second
Jesus Christ. Do they know? They have other engines right?
My heart is racing … I definitely gasped. Everyone else is still sleeping though
The engine caught fire and nobody reacted?
But it’s also dark outside so I can’t see much
She said I must’ve seen a glint of light or something
But they have to say that! Where are you?
The Bermuda Triangle, the mysterious place where everything disappears … ?
Oh no this is creeping me out
I’m basically SOBBING here thinking you died or something
Couldn’t type because of the turbulence
WHAT? STOP TEXTING AND PUT IT ON NOW!
Done. I’ve never seen that happen before!
So there IS something really wrong??
The system activated because of turbulence
How can they afford a stunt like that??
The oxygen … It smells like something is burning …
Oh god are you making this up
But it’s ok now. We can all take them off
They should give you back your money
People going back to sleep … But the stewards look really worried
Well of course! The masks shouldn’t just fall down!!
It’s still shaking … And it’s become really silent
Oh my god Rob what is going on up there
We’re in the middle of the ocean
You know what I just noticed?
The plane is still in the EXACTLY SAME position as the last time I looked
We haven’t moved AT ALL … according to the computer
Hard to say it’s all dark outside
Stewards just keep saying it’s fine
And everyone else still seems to be sleeping
Plane is rocking all over the place
And this ominous sound … like fate
Ok I’m officially freaked out now
Didn’t I tell you to NOT DO THAT anymore
I wish you were here with me, cuddled up watching House of Cards
What kind of f*cked up flight is this?
The engine DID catch fire, some sort of malfunction
The eerie sound is the wind whistling through it
So you did hear something! You were right!
And when it burst, some pieces hit the rest of the plane
One of them put a hole in the kerosene reservoir
They shut down some of the systems to save on energy
That’s why the map wasn’t working, and the air is thin
We’re stranded … They’ve called for help
But apparently we’re too far out for anyone to reach us on time …
They are trying to figure out how and when to tell the passengers
Everything was fine a minute ago
My battery is dying but I’m going to try to call you to hear your voice
If it dies before we get to speak …
I love you so much. Thank you for everything
